<body>

  <section class="d-flex justify-content-center mb-3">
    <section class="mainContent">

      <section class="row mb-5">
        <div class="col">
          <div class="card searchStyle">
            <img class="card-img" src="../images/SearchBackground.jpg" height="300px" alt="Searchbar Img">
            <div class="card-img-overlay d-flex mx-auto align-items-center col-lg-10 col-12">
              <div class="input-group input-group-lg">
                <div class="input-group-prepend">
                  <button class="input-group-text" id="searchBtn" onclick="getSearchResults()">Search</button>
                </div>
                <input type="text" class="form-control" id="searchInp" aria-label="SearchBar">
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="row justify-content-center mt-5 mb-1">
        <h1 class="text-light">
          <i class="fas fa-xs fa-leaf fa-flip-horizontal"></i>
          Plant Genus Categories
          <i class="fas fa-xs fa-leaf"></i>
        </h1>
      </section>

      <section class="row">
        <div class="card-deck justify-content-center d-sm-block d-md-block d-lg-flex d-xl-flex">

          <div class="card elementShadow align-items-center col-lg-4 col-auto my-lg-1 my-md-5 my-sm-5">
            <img class="card-img-top mt-4 iconSizing" src="../Icons/abiesPlants.png" alt="Abies Plants">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h2 class="card-title d-flex justify-content-center">Abies Plants</h2>
              <p class="card-text">Abies are a genus of 48–56 species of evergreen coniferous trees in the family
                Pinaceae. Characterized by flattish leaves, smooth circular leaf scars, and erect cones, and are valued
                for their wood</p>
            </div>
            <button id="abiesBtn" class="btn text-light btnColoring btn-lg mb-3" role="button" aria-pressed="true">View
              Abies
              Plants</button>
          </div>

          <div class="card elementShadow align-items-center col-lg-4 col-auto my-lg-1 my-md-5 my-sm-5">
            <img class="card-img-top mt-4 iconSizing" src="../Icons/carexPlants.png" alt="Carex Plants">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h2 class="card-title d-flex justify-content-center">Carex Plants</h2>
              <p class="card-text">Carex is a vast genus of more than 2,000 species of grass-like plants in the
                family Cyperaceae, commonly known as sedges. The leaves of Carex comprise a blade, which extends away
                from the stalk, and a sheath, which encloses part of the stalk.</p>
            </div>
            <button id="carexBtn" class="btn text-light btnColoring btn-lg mb-3" role="button" aria-pressed="true">View
              Carex
              Plants</button>
          </div>

          <div class="card elementShadow align-items-center col-lg-4 col-auto my-lg-1 my-md-5 my-sm-5">
            <img class="card-img-top mt-4 iconSizing" src="../Icons/fraxinusPlants.png" alt="Fraxinus Plants">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h2 class="card-title d-flex justify-content-center">Fraxinus Plants</h2>
              <p class="card-text">Fraxinus is a genus of flowering plants in the olive and lilac family, Oleaceae. It
                contains 45–65 species of usually medium to large trees, mostly deciduous, though a number of
                subtropical species are evergreen.</p>
            </div>
            <button class="btn text-light btnColoring btn-lg mb-3" role="button" aria-pressed="true">View
              Fraxinus
              Plants</button>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="row justify-content-center mt-5 mb-1">
        <h1 class="text-light">
          <i class="fas fa-xs fa-circle"></i>
          Minor Plant Kingdoms
          <i class="fas fa-xs fa-circle"></i>
        </h1>
      </section>

      <section class="row">
        <div class="card-deck justify-content-center d-sm-block d-md-block d-lg-flex d-xl-flex">

          <div class="card elementShadow align-items-center col-lg-3 col-auto my-lg-1 my-md-5 my-sm-5">
            <img class="card-img-top mt-4 iconSizing" src="../Icons/bryophyte.png" alt="Bryophyte Plants">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h2 class="card-title d-flex justify-content-center">Bryophytes</h2>
              <p class="card-text">Bryophytes are an informal group consisting of three divisions of non-vascular land
                plants known as liverworts, hornworts and mosses. They are characteristically limited in
                size and prefer moist habitats although they can survive in drier environments.</p>
            </div>
            <button class="btn text-light btnColoring btn-lg mb-3" role="button" aria-pressed="true">View
              Bryophytes</button>
          </div>

          <div class="card elementShadow align-items-center col-lg-3 col-auto my-lg-1 my-md-5 my-sm-5">
            <img class="card-img-top mt-4 iconSizing" src="../Icons/fern.png" alt="Fern Plants">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h2 class="card-title d-flex justify-content-center">Ferns</h2>
              <p class="card-text">A fern is a member of a group of vascular plants that reproduce via spores and have
                neither seeds nor flowers. Ferns have complex leaves called megaphylls producing coiled fiddleheads that
                uncoil and expand into fronds.</p>
            </div>
            <button class="btn text-light btnColoring btn-lg mb-3" role="button" aria-pressed="true">View Ferns</button>
          </div>

          <div class="card elementShadow align-items-center col-lg-3 col-auto my-lg-1 my-md-5 my-sm-5">
            <img class="card-img-top mt-4 iconSizing" src="../Icons/angiosperms.png" alt="Angiosperms Plants">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h2 class="card-title d-flex justify-content-center">Angiosperms</h2>
              <p class="card-text">Angiosperms otherwise known as the flowering plants are the most diverse group of
                land plants. They are distinguished from gymnosperms by characteristics including flowers, endosperm
                within their seeds, and the production of fruits that contain the seeds.</p>
            </div>
            <button class="btn text-light btnColoring btn-lg mb-3" role="button" aria-pressed="true">View
              Angiosperms</button>
          </div>

          <div class="card elementShadow align-items-center col-lg-3 col-auto my-lg-1 my-md-5 my-sm-5">
            <img class="card-img-top mt-4 iconSizing" src="../Icons/gymnosperm.png" alt="Gymnosperm Plants">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h2 class="card-title d-flex justify-content-center">Gymnosperm</h2>
              <p class="card-text">The gymnosperms are a group of seed-producing plants. The non-encased condition of
                their seeds contrasts with angiosperms, which are enclosed within an ovary. Gymnosperm seeds develop
                on the surface of scales or leaves, which are often modified to form cones.</p>
            </div>
            <button class="btn text-light btnColoring btn-lg mb-3" role="button" aria-pressed="true">View
              Gymnosperms</button>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

